We found that Debian-packaged uWSGI is missing one param in uwsgi_params so you should use this instead:<p><pre><code>    location / {
        uwsgi_pass <xxx>;
        include uwsgi_params;
        uwsgi_param UWSGI_SCHEME $scheme;
    }
</code></pre>
Without the UWSGI_SCHEME part, Django's Request.get_absolute_uri will return URIs starting with 'http' even if your site is served over HTTPS.
